# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Generated artefact: data/modules/index.js
#
# This file is the merged output of `data/modules/postbuild.js` (TypeScript
# build + legacy_runtime.js + every other top-level *.js module). It is
# 77 000+ lines long and merging two parents line-by-line is what produced
# the cbeacf6 outage (Nakama refused to start the JS runtime because the
# merge committed `<<<<<<< HEAD` markers into the bundle).
#
# Two safety nets are wired here:
#
#   1. `merge=regen-modules-index`
#      Custom merge driver — defined in scripts/git-merge-regen-index.sh —
#      ignores both sides and re-runs `node postbuild.js` so the output
#      always matches the source files. Activate it once per clone with:
#        scripts/setup-hooks.sh
#      (or manually: `git config merge.regen-modules-index.driver
#       'scripts/git-merge-regen-index.sh %A'`).
#
#   2. `linguist-generated=true`
#      Hides the file from PR diff views on GitHub so reviewers stop
#      manually 'fixing' a generated file.
#
# Same treatment for the TS compile output committed for offline builds.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
data/modules/index.js          merge=regen-modules-index linguist-generated=true
data/modules/build/index.js    merge=regen-modules-index linguist-generated=true
data/modules/build/index.d.ts  linguist-generated=true
